cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a prediction model for building energy consumption using support vector machine (SVM), which is a machine learning algorithm falling under the category of supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of a data-driven model and a relevant days data selection method based on Dynamic Time Warping, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the application of the model to a case study of an office building, which falls under the category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the use of a pseudo dynamic model to encompass thermal inertia of the building, which falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of the prediction model into a building's energy management system, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
